.NET Framework 3.5.name: VRTK_CustomJointGrabAttach
.NET Framework 3.5.summary: The Custom Joint Grab Attach script allows a custom joint to be provided for the grab attach mechanic.
.NET Framework 3.5.remarks:
The custom joint is placed on the interactable object and at runtime the joint is copied into a JointHolder game object that becomes a child of the interactable object.

 The custom joint is then copied from this `JointHolder` to the interactable object when a grab happens and is removed when a grab ends.
.NET Framework 3.5.example: VRTK/Examples/021_Controller_GrabbingObjectsWithJoints demonstrates this grab attach mechanic on the Lamp object in the scene.
